
service(8)                  System Manager's Manual                 service(8)



NNAAMMEE
       service - run a System V init script


SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       sseerrvviiccee _S_C_R_I_P_T _C_O_M_M_A_N_D [_O_P_T_I_O_N_S]

       sseerrvviiccee ----ssttaattuuss--aallll

       sseerrvviiccee ----hheellpp | --hh | ----vveerrssiioonn


DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       sseerrvviiccee runs a System V init script or upstart job in as predictable an
       environment as possible, removing most environment variables  and  with
       the current working directory set to //.

       The  _S_C_R_I_P_T  parameter  specifies  a  System  V init script, located in
       //eettcc//iinniitt..dd//_S_C_R_I_P_T, or the name of an upstart  job  in  /etc/init.  The
       existence of an upstart job of the same name as a script in /etc/init.d
       will cause the upstart job to take precedence over the  init.d  script.
       The  supported values of _C_O_M_M_A_N_D depend on the invoked script.  sseerrvviiccee
       passes _C_O_M_M_A_N_D and _O_P_T_I_O_N_S to the init script unmodified.  For  upstart
       jobs,  start, stop, status, are passed through to their upstart equiva‐
       lents. Restart will call the upstart 'stop' for the job, followed imme‐
       diately by the 'start', and will exit with the return code of the start
       command.  All scripts should support at least the ssttaarrtt and  ssttoopp  com‐
       mands.   As a special case, if _C_O_M_M_A_N_D is ----ffuullll--rreessttaarrtt, the script is
       run twice, first with the ssttoopp command, then with  the  ssttaarrtt  command.
       This option has no effect on upstart jobs.

       sseerrvviiccee ----ssttaattuuss--aallll runs all init scripts, in alphabetical order, with
       the ssttaattuuss command. This option only calls status  for  sysvinit  jobs,
       upstart jobs can be queried in a similar manner with iinniittccttll lliisstt'.


EEXXIITT CCOODDEESS
       sseerrvviiccee calls the init script and returns the status returned by it.


FFIILLEESS
       //eettcc//iinniitt..dd
              The directory containing System V init scripts.

       //eettcc//iinniitt
              The directory containing upstart jobs.


EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTT
       LLAANNGG, TTEERRMM
              The only environment variables passed to the init scripts.


SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _/_e_t_c_/_i_n_i_t_._d_/_s_k_e_l_e_t_o_n,
       uuppddaattee--rrcc..dd(8),
       iinniitt(8),
       iinnvvookkee--rrcc..dd(8).
       iinniittccttll(8).



